data.title: Cleveland's DigitalC initiative connects 7,000 homes and 17,000 residents, 85% towards 2025 goal. #digitalinclusion
data.description: Cleveland's citywide broadband initiative, led by DigitalC, has successfully connected almost 7,000 homes and over 17,000 residents. This progress puts them at 85% of their 2025 goal. According to news released on October 31, 2025, DigitalC, a nonprofit chosen by the City of Cleveland for this project, continues to make significant strides in providing internet access to the community.

data.title: ELGi to showcase compressed air solutions for automotive aftermarket at SEMA Show 2025, Booth #12639 in Las Vegas.
data.description: ELGi Compressors USA (ELGi) is set to showcase its lineup of air compressors and air treatment systems tailored for the automotive aftermarket sector at the SEMA Show in Las Vegas, Booth #12639. The exhibition will feature various products geared towards the industry, such as the EN15 Duplex (20 hp) rotary screw air compressor, the AB55 (75hp) oil-free rotary screw air compressor, the D185T4F tow-behind portable air compressor, and the AR N Series refrigerated air dryer. Attendees can explore these offerings designed specifically for the automotive segment.

data.title: Prospera highlights small business success in Florida with support from Duke Energy - 2025 event celebrates growth.
data.description: A recent event held in Tampa, Florida on October 31, 2025, brought together leaders and business champions in support of small business growth and economic opportunities. The annual signature event, hosted by Prospera and presented by Duke Energy, highlighted success stories and aimed to promote collaboration for mutual prosperity. The event, titled 2025 Prospera Success Stories: Together We Thrive, emphasized the importance of unity in fostering a thriving business environment. This gathering underscored the significance of small businesses in driving economic growth and featured discussions on strategies to enhance opportunities for entrepreneurs. The event attracted a significant number of attendees, including key figures from the business community, showcasing a strong commitment to empowering small businesses.

data.title: Former CIA COO Maura Burns to speak at Mount St. Mary's University in the Mark Drever Lecture Series. EMMITSBURG, Md., Oct. 31, 2025.

data.title: Experts at RenderCon delve into how AI impacts creativity, human experience, and reshapes art, science, and society.
data.description: During RenderCon, specialists delved into the implications of AI on creativity and human experience, highlighting its pivotal role in transforming art, science, and society. The event drew attention from numerous attendees eager to learn about the intersection of technology and innovation. Key themes included the evolution of AI in various sectors and its influence on the future landscape. The discussions focused on the significant advancements in AI capabilities and the potential it holds for further development. Overall, experts shed light on the growing importance of AI in shaping our world, with attendees gaining valuable insights into its multifaceted impact.

data.title: TTM Technologies, Inc. wins 2 awards from Global Electronics Association at 2025 IPC CEMAC Conference for outstanding service.
data.description: TTM Technologies, Inc. scooped up two prestigious awards from the Global Electronics Association during the recent 2025 IPC CEMAC Conference. This recognition comes as TTM Technologies, Inc. continues to thrive, with an annual revenue exceeding $1.5 billion and a strong presence in key global markets. The awards underscore TTM's commitment to innovation and excellence in the ever-evolving world of electronics.

data.title: Wilderness Mountain Water Co. reduces energy use by 50% and increases water canning by 150% with ELGi compressor.
data.description: In Charlotte, North Carolina, Wilderness Mountain Water Company (Wilderness) has utilized a historic artesian well in Virginia to produce hundreds of millions of cans of acclaimed water over the past three years. Following the installation of an ELGi oil-free air compressor, their water sourcing and packaging operations have seen significant improvements. The implementation of a single ELGi AB55 compressor has resulted in reduced utility costs, increased productivity, and enhanced product quality for Wilderness.
